result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Cadias Dubage Dumellow Jackson was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Cadias Dubage Dumellow Jackson was found guilty of Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
